**Microctronoller selection**

**Microctronoller selection**

I have decided to choose the ESP32 because it has low power consumption and supports both WiFi and Bluetooth. I can control the motors via Wi-Fi on my phone. I will send a signal to Christopher and receive a response from Jacob via Bluetooth. I will be sending and receiving data from Caleb’s board.  
![][image1]  
Table1: ESP32-S3-WROOM-1-N4 diagram

| Component | Pros | Cons |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| ESP32-S3-WROOM-1-N4 ![][image2] | Wifi and Bluetooth enabled Easier to control the motors with a motor driver Budget friendly | Can’t make more more complex subsystem High power usage |
| PIC18F47Q10 $2.63![][image3] | Stable control applications Good peripheral control Less power will be needed | Costly Does not have wifi and Bluetooth mounted Limited memory |
